  "title": "Tender Engineer, L6 M&E Contractor",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Support pre-tender and tender phases for all M&amp;E trades, raising queries or amendments to influence clients or consultants where possible.</li>\n  <li>Preparation, review, and submission of tenders for mechanical, electrical, and ELV systems, ensuring completeness, quality, and compliance with technical and risk requirements.</li>\n  <li>Enhance and consolidate quotes to meet target win prices, preparing a tender cost summary for management approval, and ensuring margin protection, while also preparing for tender interview presentations to support negotiations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Engineering/QS related studies</li>\n  <li>At least 1-3 years of working experiences in Quantity Surveying/Tender Management for M&amp;E Contractor environment</li>\n  <li>Experience in handling building construction projects will be advantageous</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If this opportunity aligns with your skills and experience, please submit your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Dickson KOH, </strong>EA Registration R1103367</p>\n<p>www.bayesrecruitment.com</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>",
